WEBVTT

1
00:00:14.916 --> 00:00:19.291
You show up to the celebration
whether you like it or not.

2
00:00:19.375 --> 00:00:23.083
It's over between you and I.
You need to accept that.

3
00:00:29.416 --> 00:00:31.375
That dog.

4
00:00:31.458 --> 00:00:34.958
That bastard
actually called the police on me?

5
00:00:37.375 --> 00:00:39.208
Yes. I did scratch his car.

6
00:00:39.291 --> 00:00:42.625
But after everything he has done to me?

7
00:00:42.708 --> 00:00:45.958
He was busy sleeping around
with all those bitches he came across.

8
00:00:46.041 --> 00:00:47.916
Then he gives me HIV?

9
00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.333
AIDS?

10
00:00:50.416 --> 00:00:52.166
What I did was not enough.

11
00:00:52.250 --> 00:00:55.375
I should have grabbed him
by the balls and castrated them

12
00:00:55.458 --> 00:00:57.583
because that's what makes him feel
like a man.

13
00:00:57.666 --> 00:00:59.333
We'll see if he can cheat then.

14
00:01:02.916 --> 00:01:04.500
You must think I'm crazy. right?

15
00:01:06.208 --> 00:01:07.666
I am not crazy.

16
00:01:15.458 --> 00:01:16.458
And then you?

17
00:01:16.541 --> 00:01:19.166
What's a beautiful lady
like you doing here?

18
00:01:25.416 --> 00:01:28.083
My husband's side chick got me arrested.

19
00:01:28.958 --> 00:01:32.833
I burnt down our old house
that we used to live in.

20
00:01:32.916 --> 00:01:35.666
with both of them still in it.

21
00:01:38.166 --> 00:01:40.916
Girl. you are the bomb.

22
00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:43.333
You burnt it? You burnt the house down?

23
00:01:43.416 --> 00:01:45.166
Why didn't I think of this?

24
00:01:45.250 --> 00:01:47.875
I should've burnt
his house down. the bastard.

25
00:01:47.958 --> 00:01:51.000
-It's a pity they survived.
-Bastard.

26
00:01:51.083 --> 00:01:52.208
You know.

27
00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:54.250
we have a party.

28
00:01:55.625 --> 00:01:58.375
To celebrate our 20th anniversary.

29
00:01:58.458 --> 00:02:00.875
And it's happening soon. in a few hours.

30
00:02:00.958 --> 00:02:02.041
And me.

31
00:02:02.875 --> 00:02:03.875
I'm here.

32
00:02:04.958 --> 00:02:06.833
And what about my kids?

33
00:02:06.916 --> 00:02:09.625
Nkazimulo is just a baby.

34
00:02:11.208 --> 00:02:14.583
Everything I've worked for
my whole entire life…

35
00:02:16.625 --> 00:02:18.333
I'm going to lose it.

36
00:02:22.666 --> 00:02:24.666
Happy anniversary. Sis.

37
00:02:31.416 --> 00:02:32.875
You called the cops?

38
00:02:34.625 --> 00:02:35.708
What were you thinking?

39
00:02:37.083 --> 00:02:38.916
I don't get you.

40
00:02:41.708 --> 00:02:42.875
Jonas.

41
00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.250
-What did you want me to do?
-Listen. and let me tell you something.

42
00:02:47.333 --> 00:02:48.875
As the Gomoras.

43
00:02:48.958 --> 00:02:51.583
we don't air our dirty laundry in public.

44
00:02:51.666 --> 00:02:53.041
-At all. Yes.
-Really?

45
00:02:53.125 --> 00:02:55.083
Was I supposed to lie to the cops?

46
00:02:55.166 --> 00:02:57.250
After we both almost got burnt alive?

47
00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:03.916
I don't like
a woman that doesn't listen to me.

48
00:03:06.250 --> 00:03:09.041
Oh. you think this is funny?

49
00:03:09.125 --> 00:03:10.625
Jonas.

50
00:03:10.708 --> 00:03:12.208
So. I'm the bad guy now?

51
00:03:12.291 --> 00:03:14.791
While Joyce almost burnt us alive?

52
00:03:14.875 --> 00:03:17.791
She's the mother of my children.

53
00:03:19.708 --> 00:03:21.541
-Dad! Dad!
-Dad!

54
00:03:22.541 --> 00:03:23.666
Mpume? Menzi?

55
00:03:23.750 --> 00:03:27.416
Wow. Mom is in jail. and you're here
lounging like nothing's wrong.

56
00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:31.125
-It must be nice.
-You chose to do nothing and not help her?

57
00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:36.208
You don't care about us.

58
00:03:37.416 --> 00:03:39.791
Listen. Mpume.

59
00:03:40.625 --> 00:03:42.375
I will fix this. okay?

60
00:03:43.833 --> 00:03:44.833
I promise you.

61
00:03:47.125 --> 00:03:49.958
The event only starts at 3:00.
Why are we leaving so early?

62
00:03:50.041 --> 00:03:54.208
Hey. I want to arrive early
so I can be in the front-row seat.

63
00:03:54.291 --> 00:03:57.041
Joyce is celebrating an anniversary
with a man she doesn't live with.

64
00:03:57.125 --> 00:04:00.666
-She's really lost her mind.
-I don't care about all of that.

65
00:04:00.750 --> 00:04:03.666
Oh. no!
Mpume says Aunt Joyce has been arrested.

66
00:04:03.750 --> 00:04:05.083
-What?
-What?

67
00:04:05.958 --> 00:04:08.000
-Where did you see that?
-Right here.

68
00:04:08.083 --> 00:04:10.500
Apparently. she's the one
who burnt the old Gomora house. Ma.

69
00:04:10.583 --> 00:04:12.291
Wow.

70
00:04:12.375 --> 00:04:14.625
I underestimated Joyce.

71
00:04:14.708 --> 00:04:15.958
That means there's no party.

72
00:04:16.041 --> 00:04:17.291
Let's forget about all of this.

73
00:04:17.375 --> 00:04:21.166
-Yeah. you're right.
-Wait. wait. wait. We're going there.

74
00:04:21.250 --> 00:04:23.375
Now I'm really eager
to see what's going to happen.

75
00:04:23.458 --> 00:04:24.458
-Huh?
-Yes!

76
00:04:24.541 --> 00:04:27.083
You think I'd want to miss that drama?
Come on. let's go.

77
00:04:27.166 --> 00:04:28.708
-Let's go then.
-Let's go. children.

78
00:04:28.791 --> 00:04:29.791
But. Mom…

79
00:04:55.333 --> 00:04:56.333
Joyce Gomora!

80
00:04:57.375 --> 00:04:58.833
You got bailed.

81
00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:03.875
Come. Your husband is outside.

82
00:05:03.958 --> 00:05:05.875
Joyce Gomora?

83
00:05:05.958 --> 00:05:06.958
No. man!

84
00:05:07.583 --> 00:05:10.166
Yeah. I knew you looked familiar.

85
00:05:13.833 --> 00:05:15.166
Listen. girl.

86
00:05:16.208 --> 00:05:19.625
You know what? I'll DM you. okay?
You must respond.

87
00:05:41.083 --> 00:05:42.666
Hold on. Joyce.

88
00:05:46.791 --> 00:05:47.791
My publicist

89
00:05:48.833 --> 00:05:50.500
is on standby as we speak

90
00:05:51.625 --> 00:05:53.750
to take our joint statement

91
00:05:53.833 --> 00:05:56.208
and to announce our divorce.

92
00:06:01.458 --> 00:06:03.041
Oh. my God.

93
00:06:10.041 --> 00:06:12.083
You know what. Jonas? I'm tired

94
00:06:12.875 --> 00:06:18.041
of trying to fight whatever potion
this girl has clearly used on you.

95
00:06:19.083 --> 00:06:21.125
You can have your joint statement.

96
00:06:23.291 --> 00:06:25.625
I'll sign your divorce papers.

97
00:06:29.125 --> 00:06:32.833
Yeah.

98
00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:40.958
But…

99
00:06:42.708 --> 00:06:44.208
only after the party.

100
00:06:44.291 --> 00:06:45.958
-Party?
-Mm-hmm.

101
00:06:48.250 --> 00:06:49.958
Do you want your freedom or not?

102
00:06:50.541 --> 00:06:53.000
No. no. no. no. Not in that way.

103
00:06:57.500 --> 00:06:59.875
You have 34 voice messages.

104
00:06:59.958 --> 00:07:01.083
Hey. Joyce.

105
00:07:01.166 --> 00:07:03.666
I just want to confirm
my attendance to the anniversary event.

106
00:07:03.750 --> 00:07:05.250
Joyce. Trinity here.

107
00:07:05.333 --> 00:07:06.958
I just want to confirm my…

108
00:07:07.041 --> 00:07:10.666
Joyce. we're definitely going
with the pink and white arrangement.

109
00:07:11.583 --> 00:07:14.958
Joyce. I need
to go over the final touch-ups.

110
00:07:15.791 --> 00:07:18.208
Nkazimulo.
will he be walking you down the aisle?

111
00:07:20.958 --> 00:07:22.541
Whatever.

112
00:07:23.833 --> 00:07:26.375
Hi. You're speaking to Joyce.

113
00:07:26.458 --> 00:07:29.916
Yes. No. no. I'm all right.

114
00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:32.458
I wanted to talk to you about something.

115
00:07:32.541 --> 00:07:36.875
I know what I'm going to say will be…
…a bit unusual.

116
00:07:36.958 --> 00:07:37.958
But…

117
00:07:39.541 --> 00:07:40.666
…I need your help.

118
00:07:46.708 --> 00:07:47.791
-Ma.
-Mmm. baby.

119
00:07:47.875 --> 00:07:49.916
So. you're really going ahead
with this. Ma?

120
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:53.000
Tell me. how long are you going to let
that man of yours treat you this way?

121
00:07:53.083 --> 00:07:55.833
That man you're talking about
is your father. Let's not forget that.

122
00:07:55.916 --> 00:07:58.000
Oh. Mom.
you deserve so much better than this.

123
00:07:58.083 --> 00:07:59.666
My goodness! What's wrong with you?

124
00:08:00.250 --> 00:08:02.250
This is marriage.

125
00:08:02.333 --> 00:08:04.708
-You don't walk away so easily.
-In other words. you're saying that

126
00:08:04.791 --> 00:08:08.666
if another man were to do the same thing
that Dad is doing to you. you'd be happy?

127
00:08:28.458 --> 00:08:32.166
My brother. Give me two.

128
00:08:35.708 --> 00:08:38.791
There's Mrs. Party.

129
00:08:38.875 --> 00:08:42.000
She's acting like
everything is fine. She's so fake.

130
00:08:42.083 --> 00:08:44.958
But. Mom. you have to admit.
she looks good. though.

131
00:08:45.041 --> 00:08:46.875
You're pissing me off now.

132
00:08:46.958 --> 00:08:47.958
Thank you.

133
00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:50.250
Thank you. Ma.

134
00:09:22.666 --> 00:09:24.458
What if he doesn't arrive. Thembi?

135
00:09:24.541 --> 00:09:27.958
Friend. maybe you should wait for him
in the bridal suite. you know?

136
00:09:28.041 --> 00:09:29.875
-Just in case this person…
-Uh-uh.

137
00:09:45.958 --> 00:09:48.541
Joyce. where's Mr. Party?

138
00:09:48.625 --> 00:09:50.541
I'm very excited to meet him in person.

139
00:09:50.625 --> 00:09:53.916
Uh. he's on his way.
You'll see him shortly.

140
00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:56.333
Really? He's coming?

141
00:09:56.958 --> 00:09:58.791
Matipa.

142
00:09:59.416 --> 00:10:00.833
I'm so happy to see you.

143
00:10:00.916 --> 00:10:04.250
How could I dare miss
such a big and beautiful event?

144
00:10:04.333 --> 00:10:06.333
-Mmm.
-This is Matipa.

145
00:10:06.416 --> 00:10:08.875
-Uh. she's a…
-Family friend.

146
00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:11.166
Of the Gomoras.

147
00:10:11.250 --> 00:10:13.625
Actually. closer than that.

148
00:10:14.208 --> 00:10:16.250
You see. Joyce and I are practically

149
00:10:16.916 --> 00:10:17.916
sisters.

150
00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:19.541
You see that?

151
00:10:19.625 --> 00:10:22.708
Joyce. aren't you gonna make
the big announcement?

152
00:10:23.750 --> 00:10:26.416
-What announcement?
-Don't worry. I'll fill you in.

153
00:10:27.083 --> 00:10:29.333
You see. as we're standing here. Joyce

154
00:10:30.458 --> 00:10:31.625
and Jonas

155
00:10:33.166 --> 00:10:34.166
are

156
00:10:35.125 --> 00:10:36.916
-officially…
-Greetings.

157
00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:40.041
Ooh!

158
00:10:40.125 --> 00:10:41.791
Ah. Thembi. You're here.

159
00:10:41.875 --> 00:10:43.458
-Ma.
-My son.

160
00:10:43.541 --> 00:10:45.375
Yeah. My wife.

161
00:10:46.333 --> 00:10:47.333
My love.

162
00:10:47.833 --> 00:10:48.875
My love.

163
00:10:54.166 --> 00:10:56.083
-Don't you want it?
-Not here. love.

164
00:10:56.166 --> 00:10:57.208
What?

165
00:10:57.291 --> 00:11:00.208
-That's late-night activities. Not here.
-Ah. stop it.

166
00:11:02.083 --> 00:11:04.083
-How rude of us.
-Ah.

167
00:11:04.166 --> 00:11:06.958
This is Trinity Cele.
the one I'm always talking about.

168
00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:09.958
-Oh. Cele. You look gorgeous.
-Yes.

169
00:11:10.041 --> 00:11:12.958
-Yes.
-Aren't you the one getting married here?

170
00:11:13.041 --> 00:11:15.125
-My goodness!
-I'm just asking.

171
00:11:15.208 --> 00:11:17.375
-We'll be back.
-We'll be right back. Enjoy yourselves.

172
00:11:17.458 --> 00:11:19.208
-Mr. Gomora.
-We'll be right back.

173
00:11:19.291 --> 00:11:20.958
-We're happy to see you.
-Thank you. sir.

174
00:11:21.041 --> 00:11:22.791
-It's good to see you. sir.
-God bless you.

175
00:11:22.875 --> 00:11:25.291
-Amen. Amen.
-You can go ahead and have a seat.

176
00:11:25.375 --> 00:11:26.791
-We'll be right there with you.
-Amen.

177
00:11:26.875 --> 00:11:29.041
Oh. so the wild dog decided
to finally come?

178
00:11:29.125 --> 00:11:30.333
-Oh. I'm the dog?
-Yes. you are.

179
00:11:30.416 --> 00:11:32.833
-Don't you know that?
-How would this dog not come. though?

180
00:11:32.916 --> 00:11:35.416
Especially because you spoke
to the minister's wife

181
00:11:35.500 --> 00:11:37.250
-to threaten my tender.
-Mm-hmm.

182
00:11:37.333 --> 00:11:39.958
-Joyce. how low can you go?
-You know what?

183
00:11:40.041 --> 00:11:43.333
I'd even go
to the depths of hell if I had to. Jonas.

184
00:11:43.416 --> 00:11:46.083
-Hell is exactly where you belong.
-Yes. hell. Don't you dare tell me that.

185
00:11:46.166 --> 00:11:48.166
-Look at this. What?
-Hey. hey. hey. don't.

186
00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:49.666
-Don't touch it.
-I'm fixing my husband.

187
00:11:49.750 --> 00:11:51.000
-I'm your husband now?
-My husband…

188
00:11:51.083 --> 00:11:53.791
-Yes! It's our company together. Jonas.
-You're holding my company hostage. Oh.

189
00:11:53.875 --> 00:11:55.583
It's like that now.

190
00:11:56.166 --> 00:11:57.958
-Uh. no!
-Did you see me? Oh!

191
00:11:58.041 --> 00:12:02.166
-Oh. my. Minister!
-Greetings.

192
00:12:02.250 --> 00:12:04.583
-Hello. darling.
-Who are we to be graced by your presence?

193
00:12:04.666 --> 00:12:07.583
-You look so good.
-Thank you. You look good too.

194
00:12:07.666 --> 00:12:08.666
-For us?
-Thank you very much.

195
00:12:08.750 --> 00:12:11.291
Okay. now I want to
thank you very much for partnering

196
00:12:11.375 --> 00:12:13.375
-with us on the bridge construction.
-Yes.

197
00:12:13.458 --> 00:12:15.375
-Right.
-And this tender is very important to…

198
00:12:15.458 --> 00:12:16.916
You got this tender

199
00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:20.750
because my husband and I
believe in the both of you.

200
00:12:20.833 --> 00:12:22.875
-Oh.
-And the fact that you guys believe

201
00:12:22.958 --> 00:12:25.250
in family principles and values.

202
00:12:25.333 --> 00:12:28.458
My admiration for Joyce as a wife
goes way back.

203
00:12:28.541 --> 00:12:31.708
We backed you. Jonas and Joyce.

204
00:12:32.541 --> 00:12:34.333
-You're a package.
-Mmm.

205
00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:36.333
Mm-hmm.

206
00:12:37.458 --> 00:12:39.041
-Let me take you to your seat…
-Oh. thank you.

207
00:12:39.125 --> 00:12:41.333
-…so we can enjoy the festivities.
-Of course. Yes.

208
00:12:41.416 --> 00:12:43.750
-My hubby. do you like it?
-All right. All right.

209
00:12:43.833 --> 00:12:46.083
-My brother-in-law.
-My sister-in-law.

210
00:12:46.166 --> 00:12:48.791
My sister-in-law.

211
00:12:48.875 --> 00:12:50.250
And then?

212
00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:51.333
What's going on here?

213
00:12:53.041 --> 00:12:55.000
She ran off to the minister.

214
00:12:55.083 --> 00:12:56.208
-Huh?
-Mm-hmm.

215
00:12:56.291 --> 00:12:58.916
She got him to threaten the tender.

216
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:00.666
-You know what that means?
-What?

217
00:13:00.750 --> 00:13:03.291
We're renewing our vows today.

218
00:13:07.291 --> 00:13:09.375
It's going down.

219
00:13:29.958 --> 00:13:31.875
"Love is patient.

220
00:13:32.541 --> 00:13:33.791
It is kind.

221
00:13:34.333 --> 00:13:37.458
Love does not envy.

222
00:13:38.791 --> 00:13:41.041
Love is not proud.

223
00:13:42.750 --> 00:13:46.291
It does not dishonour others.

224
00:13:46.833 --> 00:13:49.125
It is not self-seeking.

225
00:13:49.708 --> 00:13:52.791
Love does not delight in evil.

226
00:13:53.375 --> 00:13:55.458
But rejoices the truth.

227
00:13:57.458 --> 00:14:01.541
It perseveres through everything.

228
00:14:01.625 --> 00:14:03.416
It always trusts.

229
00:14:04.625 --> 00:14:06.416
It always hopes."

230
00:14:09.958 --> 00:14:11.541
I still love you.

231
00:14:11.625 --> 00:14:14.875
I don't think I'll ever stop.

232
00:14:37.083 --> 00:14:39.041
Okay.

233
00:14:39.666 --> 00:14:41.708
Hold on.

234
00:14:41.791 --> 00:14:45.291
-No. stop it.
-Let me. What? Still.

235
00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:57.666
Everyone knows that I…
I am not a man of many words.

236
00:14:57.750 --> 00:15:00.208
However. I felt compelled

237
00:15:00.791 --> 00:15:02.708
to say something today.

238
00:15:02.791 --> 00:15:07.458
It's no secret that my younger brother
and I had a rough upbringing.

239
00:15:08.208 --> 00:15:09.541
But for him. it was worse.

240
00:15:10.916 --> 00:15:13.416
It was worse
because he was a dreamer. you know?

241
00:15:15.875 --> 00:15:17.333
But then things changed.

242
00:15:18.875 --> 00:15:20.041
Joyce arrived.

243
00:15:20.125 --> 00:15:23.125
Yes. my sister-in-law.

244
00:15:23.625 --> 00:15:24.875
This lady fought

245
00:15:24.958 --> 00:15:27.791
to open doors for this man.

246
00:15:28.333 --> 00:15:31.625
What made Jonas love this lady

247
00:15:32.291 --> 00:15:35.250
was the potential she saw in him.

248
00:15:36.250 --> 00:15:39.625
She saw that he was a great man.

249
00:15:39.708 --> 00:15:44.208
He once said. "With this woman by my side.

250
00:15:44.291 --> 00:15:46.208
I will take over the world."

251
00:15:46.875 --> 00:15:50.333
Twenty years later.
the job is not done yet.

252
00:15:51.125 --> 00:15:52.250
Keep at it.

253
00:15:53.291 --> 00:15:54.500
Conquer.

254
00:15:55.333 --> 00:15:56.916
